            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/armed-epa-agents-raiding/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " says, let alone the EU.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In addition, Italian officials are pointing out how incredibly expensive electrification is, something smaller automakers would have trouble transitioning too since they lack the economies of scale. It’s almost like this push to electrification is a move by auto giants to squeeze out the competition, leaving just a few automakers around the world. That transition, of course, would be super excellent for all us consumers since less competition means better goods and services.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
